practice_endings_ed_ing.meaning_en: the plural of foot, the lower part of a leg used for standing or walking
practice_endings_ed_ing.example_en: Ducks have webbed feet for swimming.
practice_endings_ed_ing.example_vi: Vịt có chân màng để bơi.

practice_endings_ed_ing.meaning_en: the plural of leg, the limbs used for walking or standing
practice_endings_ed_ing.meaning_vi: chân (số nhiều, của động vật hoặc người)
practice_endings_ed_ing.example_en: The crane has long legs for wading.
practice_endings_ed_ing.example_vi: Con sếu có đôi chân dài để lội nước.

practice_endings_ed_ing.example_en: The spotted frog jumped into the pond.
practice_endings_ed_ing.example_vi: Con ếch có đốm nhảy vào ao.

practice_endings_ed_ing.meaning_en: the act of moving through water using limbs or fins
practice_endings_ed_ing.example_en: Fish are swimming in the pond.

practice_endings_ed_ing.meaning_en: having skin between the toes, aiding in swimming
practice_endings_ed_ing.example_en: Ducks have webbed feet to help them swim.
practice_endings_ed_ing.example_vi: Vịt có chân màng để giúp chúng bơi.

practice_endings_ed_ing.meaning_en: the act of jumping on one or both feet
practice_endings_ed_ing.example_en: Frogs are great at hopping on land.
practice_endings_ed_ing.example_vi: Ếch rất giỏi nhảy lò cò trên cạn.

practice_endings_ed_ing.example_en: The swan has a long neck for reaching plants.
practice_endings_ed_ing.example_vi: Con thiên nga có cái cổ dài để vươn tới thực vật.

practice_endings_ed_ing.meaning_en: having great physical power or strength
practice_endings_ed_ing.example_en: The frog's strong legs help it hop far.
practice_endings_ed_ing.example_vi: Đôi chân mạnh mẽ của con ếch giúp nó nhảy xa.

practice_endings_ed_ing.meaning_en: the act of walking through water
practice_endings_ed_ing.example_en: The crane was wading in the shallow pond.
practice_endings_ed_ing.example_vi: Con sếu đang lội nước ở ao nông.
